You're in Winsdale?

189
00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:54.000
Winsley.

190
00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:56.000
Oh, Winsley. Winsdale.

191
00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:58.000
Winsley.

192
00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:00.000
Winsley.

193
00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:02.000
Sorry.

194
00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:05.000
Oh, good. So you can hear me and see me?

195
00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:07.000
Yes, Erin. Hi.

196
00:23:07.000 --> 00:23:09.000
Hi.

197
00:23:09.000 --> 00:23:12.000
So yeah, I mean, I filled out the submission.

198
00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:14.000
I used to be a fisheries observer.

199
00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:19.000
So I've got quite a good first-hand knowledge of New Zealand commercial fisheries.

200
00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:24.000
And it was common knowledge when I was an observer that boats that had observers

201
00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:30.000
caught more birds and discarded more fish

202
00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:33.000
than boats without observers.

203
00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:35.000
And it's common knowledge.

204
00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:37.000
But why is that?

205
00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:42.000
Because fishermen are incentivized to not necessarily tell the truth all the time.

206
00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:47.000
And so a big problem I have with this bill is the camera footage,

207
00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:51.000
I think needs to be available to the public.

208
00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:57.000
Because the fishers need to be held accountable.

209
00:23:57.000 --> 00:23:59.000
So that's the main issue I have.

210
00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:02.000
And the other problem I have is with the undersized fish,

211
00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:07.000
I think potentially, you know, they're just creating a market for these fish,

212
00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:09.000
maybe even incentivized catching them.

213
00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:13.000
So I think that would be a backward step.

214
00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:15.000
So yeah, those are the main two issues I have.

215
00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:18.000
Yeah, and if you have any questions.

216
00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:20.000
I do, Sose.

217
00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:23.000
Yes, thank you, Joe. Joe likes to hear the question.

218
00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:25.000
