00:56:00.199 --> 00:56:01.319
So the floor is yours.

710
00:56:02.519 --> 00:56:03.519
OK.

711
00:56:04.000 --> 00:56:05.839
My name is Cody Hunn.

712
00:56:06.400 --> 00:56:09.799
A recreational fisherman official in the Harrogate Gulf.

713
00:56:10.039 --> 00:56:11.760
A boat owner for 16 years.

714
00:56:12.360 --> 00:56:14.440
And I've been out in the water since I could crawl.

715
00:56:15.600 --> 00:56:17.360
I was taught to fish by my father

716
00:56:17.840 --> 00:56:20.880
and I'm desperately trying to pass those lessons on to my twin boys.

717
00:56:22.760 --> 00:56:26.480
Over these 16 years, I've seen a heartbreaking decline.

718
00:56:27.240 --> 00:56:30.560
10 years ago, I could shoot out after work for a quackfish

719
00:56:30.840 --> 00:56:32.960
in the Ringitoto or Monahee channels

720
00:56:33.360 --> 00:56:35.480
and easily bring home a feed for my family.

721
00:56:36.200 --> 00:56:37.200
Today.

722
00:56:37.880 --> 00:56:40.440
A whole weekend of effort often ends in a struggle

723
00:56:40.440 --> 00:56:42.040
to find even one legal fish.

724
00:56:43.040 --> 00:56:47.000
The biblical numbers of snapper the minister talks about are a fantasy.

725
00:56:47.680 --> 00:56:51.840
They certainly don't match the reality of my sounder or my chili bin.

726
00:56:54.000 --> 00:56:57.360
I'm being locked out of 12 new high protection areas

727
00:56:57.880 --> 00:57:00.480
in the name of conservation.

728
00:57:00.480 --> 00:57:04.880
I can accept that, but I cannot accept the blatant double standard

729
00:57:04.960 --> 00:57:07.480
that allows commercial ring netting and trawling

730
00:57:07.880 --> 00:57:11.200
to continue right next to or even within these zones.

731
00:57:12.800 --> 00:57:15.920
It is a gut punch as a father to tell him

732
00:57:16.320 --> 00:57:19.200
he can't take his kids fishing for a car while in these areas.

733
00:57:19.200 --> 00:57:22.160
Well, a commercial boat is allowed to come up

734
00:57:23.880 --> 00:57:25.760
and sweep up tons in the same spot.

735
00:57:26.960 --> 00:57:29.880
If it's a nursery, it should be a nursery for everyone.

736
00:57:30.680 --> 00:57:33.320
No exceptions, no loopholes

737
00:57:33.880 --> 00:57:36.800
and absolutely no special treatment for industry.

738
00:57:39.400 --> 00:57:43.760
The bill reduces transparency by making it hard to see to see camera footage.

739
00:57:44.880 --> 00:57:48.800
If the industry has nothing to hide, why lock the doors?

740
00:57:49.640 --> 00:57:52.000
I know what happens when no one's watching.

741
00:57:53.080 --> 00:57:55.840
Growing up, our family came to Waibukau.

742
00:57:56.880 --> 00:57:59.320
I vividly remember seeing commercial boats

743
00:57:59.559 --> 00:58:01.640
on the horizon near the Heninchigan Islands.

744
00:58:02.639 --> 00:58:05.319
The next day, the beach was covered in dead snapper.

745
00:58:06.599 --> 00:58:08.199
We spent the afternoon on the water

746
00:58:08.480 --> 00:58:11.199
in a trail of dead fish floating across the Breen Bay.

747
00:58:12.480 --> 00:58:15.960
The old timers at the camp told me it was standard practice

748
00:58:16.079 --> 00:58:19.920
and that if they catch a fresher batch, they dump the old stuff.

749
00:58:21.400 --> 00:58:22.400
That scared me.

750
00:58:22.799 --> 00:58:25.879
It showed me how careless and wasteful these businesses can be.

751
00:58:27.000 --> 00:58:30.879
I'm asking this committee to kill the bill, at the very least,

752
00:58:31.119 --> 00:58:35.519
remove the loopholes that allow commercial mates to keep stripping the HPAs

753
00:58:35.760 --> 00:58:38.800
while families like mine are restricted to out of fish grounds.

754
00:58:39.640 --> 00:58:42.840
Don't let our hair and hair turns be traded for commercial profit.

755
00:58:44.119 --> 00:58:45.119
Thank you.

756
00:58:46.160 --> 00:58:47.960
Thank you very much, Trotty.

757
00:58:47.960 --> 00:58:49.039
Do you have any questions?

758
00:58:49.039 --> 00:58:51.360
Got a question from Miles Anderson.

759
00:58:51.360 --> 00:58:52.360
Sure.

760
00:58:53.039 --> 00:58:54.559
Thanks for your submission, Katie.

761
00:58:55.880 --> 00:58:58.320
A couple of submitters talked about the difference

762
00:58:58.360 --> 00:59:01.039
between inshore and deep sea fisheries.

763
00:59:01.559 --> 00:59:04.920
Have you any insights into the difference of those?

764
00:59:07.120 --> 00:59:09.360
Like I'm not a professional fisherman.

765
00:59:09.360 --> 00:59:10.840
I'm recreational.

766
00:59:11.080 --> 00:59:12.080
Yeah.

767
00:59:12.559 --> 00:59:16.840
So from my point of view, it's just like I've seen the decline

768
00:59:17.280 --> 00:59:22.039
and like I just want to be able to go out and get a feed

769
00:59:22.039 --> 00:59:24.320
and take my family out and have fun on the water.

770
00:59:25.720 --> 00:59:28.039
The HPAs and stuff, I think are a great idea.

771
00:59:28.039 --> 00:59:30.360
But like I say, it has to be for everyone.

772
00:59:31.599 --> 00:59:34.880
You can't say that I can't fish there and then go get a big net

773
00:59:34.880 --> 00:59:38.599
and we'll trawl through there and take it all of us.

774
00:59:38.599 --> 00:59:41.880
I'm just about being fair and

775
00:59:42.960 --> 00:59:46.599
you know, I leave it up to the professionals to to discuss what

776
00:59:47.679 --> 00:59:49.840
you know, what sort of quota limits and things like that.

777
00:59:50.519 --> 00:59:52.880
And obviously, right for the industry.

778
00:59:54.960 --> 00:59:55.960
Thanks, Cody.

779
00:59:56.000 --> 00:59:58.800
Awesome. Thank you very much for taking the time to talk to us.

780
00:59:58.800 --> 00:59:59.800
That's awesome.

781
01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:01.000
Thank you very much.

782
01:00:01.559 --> 01:00:02.559
See you, Cody.

783
01:00:10.240 --> 01:00:11.240
Right.

784
01:00:16.240 --> 01:00:17.240
So you have any.
